    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chalices, usually unconsecrated, that are used by Christian seminarians when learning to say mass. The vessels are typically of non-precious materials, such as common metal or wood.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
